A few years back, I was having dinner alone with my Mum at a restaurant. We started talking about my life goals and purpose in life. It was at this moment when she said something so sincere and striking- “I believe my purpose in life was to bring you into this world." It was incredibly touching and this wonderful memory would forever be etched in my mind. I still think about it from time to time. My mum gave up the most important things in her life so that I could take on the most important things in mine. Thank you for all the sacrifices you have made for the family through this years, as well as the unconditional love you have shown to us! I love you, Mum! ❤️ @chelspykerman

Whenever I am in doubt, I will always ask my heart - “What should I do?” Every single time it replies: “Do what your mother would tell you to do!” My Mum has always been the guiding light in my life. One of the most memorable moments with my mum, was after my first heartbreak. I was inconsolable, and lost at times. I couldn’t eat nor sleep well, and was constantly breaking into tears. I even contemplated self-harm. 
However, my mum was constantly at my side through this whole time. She was patient with me, and gave me good advice. She cooked my favorite food, and wiped away my tears. Friends come and go, boyfriends and girlfriends love and move on, but the only person present through it all is a mother. Thank you for loving me and being the best mother I can ever ask for. I love you, Mummy. ♥️ @cerealnchocolate

text:
Circuit breaker allows me to make up for the lost time with my loved ones. 
Despite difficult times like this I'm extremely grateful that my family is safe and united with me.
previously, I've been so busy with my own life that I failed to realise how much my parents have aged.... Now is the best time when I truly get to spend quality time with family. Now is the time when we create happy memories that will last a lifetime.The basic ingredients for bonding and Happiness is the time and effort to gather together. During this time we avoid going out as my families unite and we all put our differences aside. 💕
One of my fondest memories growing up was family dinners. Especially Mother's day. We'll all sit down and eat dinner together - No matter if any of us had the best or worst day, we would stop to share food together.  It wasn’t simply eating dinner together that was remarkable, it was for all of the love, time, and patience we've put into our family dinners.
This year, I'm ready to ditch the cooking stress. Instead of slaving around the kitchen, Splendid mother's day delight from @parkroyalbeachroad Sichuan Douhua is ready to send us for the festive celebration and do all the hard work for us, leaving my loved ones to enjoy your savoury spread. 
we're looking forward to expand dinner horizons with your  favorite Chinese recipes. With a meal this impressive, it'll guaranteed to get mom's seal of approval! liked and shared  @pikushi10

text:
Hope to win for my mummy for the upcoming mother’s day

She deserves to be pampered because

She met my dad 34 years ago. She was really brave and agreed to my father to give birth to me in Singapore so that I can have a better life and education over here.

When she came over, she has faced a lot of difficulties adapting to the lifestyle as compared to her village lifestyle. Everything she has to learn from scratch such as communications and many more. 
Since we were young, she has to use her own methods of giving us English and Mandarin spellings using Thai pinyin. She also learns how to cook our Chinese food so that we can have a warm home cooked dinner when we came back from school or work.

30 years ago, her relationship with my father was turned sour.  In order for us to have a complete family, she gave up her own happiness and she bears with him for so many years till now.

When I gave birth about 4 years ago, she helped us to take care of baby from days to nights. We can see the tiredness from her eyes but she was not complaining at all. 
Last year, I brought her for checkup and from there we realized that she actually suffered from minor strokes long time ago and we children we were not aware of it. We felt so embarrass and regrets towards to our mother as she always care for us and we are not realize that she was sick all these while . The doctor asked us to admit her straightaway as her blood pressure was too high. After some checkups done at hospital, we found out that she has diabetes, high blood pressure and high cholesterol.  We asked her to stop taking care of her grandson and have a good rest at home.

She has done a lot of things and sacrifices for this family. Her efforts are very appreciated by us. I would like to thank GOD for giving us such a good mother who sacrifices so much for us and she has never expected anything back from us. @jessielim90 @sam_tan18  @april_1130
